description:
What impact do equity laws have on religious liberty? How are rights and freedoms being destroyed under a pretense of protecting rights and freedoms? How are Jesus Christs Messiahship and Godhood under attack even in Protestant churches?

In this presentation, Professor Walter J. Veith explores the many inroads that the one-world religious movement has made in religious thought and society. What is the Biblical definition of truth? Is there such a thing as absolute truth? Is humanity being conditioned to accept Antichrist under the guise of a cosmic, convergent christ? What impact have The Jesus Seminar and other programs like it had on Christians perceptions of Christ? Who is behind the movement to demote Jesus Christ?

If you thought there were differences between religions, think again. In recent times, popes have made a public show of embracing non-Christian religions. Why is the Papacy promoting acceptance of Buddhism, Islam, shamanism, and other non-Christian religions? Who will benefit from an amalgamation of all religions? Who will become the high priest of a one-world religion?
